    "Algorithm 2 Low-rank approach for Distilling an LLM onto a Pre-trained Student Input: Larger transformer model (teacher) with configuration Φ Tch & weights W Tch already finetuned for the given target task, student model with configuration Φ Std & pre-trained weights W pretrain Std, D train: fine-tuning data set for the target task, r: rank of the low-rank matrices to be learned and distillation factor α ∈ [0, 1].",
    "Loss functions: Target task loss ℓ task, knowledge distillation loss ℓ KD, feature distillation loss ℓ FD.",
    "Initialize the low-rank matrices {A 1, B 1 } for fine-tuning the student model f ΦStd weights: W Std:= W pretrain Std + A 1 * B 1, where W pretrain Std is kept frozen and only {A 1, B 1 } are learned.",
    "2: for iteration = 1, 2,... do 3: Get a mini-batch B of training examples: {(x i, y i) ∈ D train | i ∈ B}.",
